Package: BioUtils
Title: BioUtils: Tools for Biological Data Analysis and Visualization
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Spencer", "Treadway", , "spencer.treadway08@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description:
    BioUtils is an R package designed to simplify and standardize workflows in
    computational biology, bioinformatics, and biostatistics. It provides a
    collection of tools for preprocessing biological datasets (such as gene
    expression and sequencing data), performing statistical analyses, and
    generating publication-quality visualizations. By integrating commonly used
    operations into a single, consistent interface, BioUtils reduces redundancy,
    improves reproducibility, and enables researchers and students to focus more
    on biological interpretation rather than data wrangling.
